350 g Gnocchi
1 unit(s) Zucchini
56 mL Cream
113 g Baby Tomatoes
¼ cup Goat Cheese, crumbled
113 g Corn Kernels
½ tbsp Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend
½ cup Sun-Dried Tomato Pesto
2.5 tbsp Oil*
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Add gnocchi to a baking sheet with 2 tbsp oil. Toss to combine.
Roast in the middle of the oven, until tender and lightly golden, 10-12 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, roast in the middle and bottom of the oven, using 2 tbsp oil for each baking sheet.)

Cut zucchini in half, and then into 1/4-inch moons.
Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then baby tomatoes. Cook, stirring often, until blistered, 3-4 min. Season with salt and peper, then remove to a plate.
Add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter to the same pan, swirling to melt.
Add corn and zucchini. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender-crisp, 4-5 min. Season with salt and pepper.

Add Smoked Paprika-Garlic Blend to the pan. Cook, stirring constantly, until veggies are coated, 30 sec.
Add sun-dried tomato pesto, cream and 1/4 cup (1/2 cup) water to the pan. Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, 1-2 min.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove the pan from heat.
Add gnocchi. Stir to coat.

Divide gnocchi between plates.
Top with blistered tomatoes.
Sprinkle goat cheese over top.